info.description:
This Swagger Page is for the FOIA Request Portal. Information about the FOIA Agency API can be found on the API Specs page.

Authorization with API Key

Use the Authorize button below to enter your api_key if you have one. You can signup for an API key or use the following api_key for testing.

N4aCuDuJO8Ucf1FTR2EzVPZqo8NsSl1c7YLYOk8N

Agency Component Entity ID

You can use the Entity ID for Office of Information Policy in the examples below:

8216158f-8089-431d-b866-dc334e8d4758
info.title: National FOIA Portal - JSON API

get.summary: Get a List of Agency Components
get.description:
Request a list of Agency Components. The ID returned can be used to get more details about the Agency Component. Using parameters such as include and fields allow you to request complex data.

For Example:

A list of agency components with their parent agency.

https://api.foia.gov/api/agency_components?&include=agency&fields[agency]=name,abbreviation&fields[agency_component]=title,abbreviation,agency

parameters.name: fields[agency_component]
parameters.description:
You can choose which fields to include by using comma separated values in this parameter.

For Example:

This endpoint will return only the title and description.
https://api.foia.gov/api/agency_components?fields[agency_component]=title,description&api_key=N4aCuDuJO8Ucf1FTR2EzVPZqo8NsSl1c7YLYOk8N

Possible values:
title, status, abbreviation, moderation_state, description, email, submission_address

parameters.name: fields[agency]
parameters.description:
You can choose which fields to include by using comma separated values in this parameter.

For Example:

This endpoint will return only the title and description.
https://api.foia.gov/api/agency_components?fields[agency_component]=title,description&api_key=N4aCuDuJO8Ucf1FTR2EzVPZqo8NsSl1c7YLYOk8N

Possible values:
title, status, abbreviation, moderation_state, description, email, submission_address

parameters.name: page[limit]
parameters.description:
You can use page[limit] to return a maximum number of results.

Learn more about Pagination in the Drupal documentation.

parameters.name: page[offset]
parameters.description:
The offset is the result you want to start with. An offset of 3 and a page[limit] of 10 will list ten items starting from item 3. Each JSON response from the API will have built in pagination under links.

Learn more about Pagination in the Drupal documentation.

parameters.name: include
parameters.description:
Embed related entities in the JSON response under relationships.

Learn more in the documentation.

Possible values:
agency, foia_officers, field_misc, public_liaisons, paper_receiver, request_form, service_centers

post.description: You can submit FOIA Requests using the webform endpoint, but you will first need the Request Form for the Agency. Each Agency has their own rules for which fields are required. The elements object from the request_form endpoint will display the required fields for that Agency.

parameters.description: The email address of the requester.

parameters.name: name_first
parameters.description: First Name of requester.

parameters.name: name_last
parameters.description: Last Name of requester.

parameters.name: request_description
parameters.description: A description for your request.

parameters.name: request_category
parameters.description:
The request category is limited to specific options.

List of example suggestions:

  • media: 'Representative of the news media'
  • educational: 'Educational Institution'
  • scientific: 'Non-commercial scientific institution'
  • commercial: 'Commercial-use requester'
  • other: 'All other requester'

parameters.name: phone_number
parameters.description: A description for your request.
